        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Here's my response copied from my guild bulletin board. Taroo = 51 wizard, Alagorn = 22 ranger, Algoron = 13 mage, Feetsa = 40 monk, Ahkwell = 26 (soon 27 necro). </P><P>**************************************<BR>Why did you choose the class you chose? When I play D&D (back to 1979, no less), I've played 2 classes: Ranger & Wizard. Why?</P><P>Ranger: Well, we don't get plate mail, but we're usually only 5%-10% worse off than warriors & have more hp early, but less later on, but we get cool spells. They're fun. They cast, they melee, they track, etc. It's FUN. This was my first EQ character Alagorn. He was fun up until 12 or so then he started getting boring, so I poked into the magical realms.</P><P>#2 for me was Algoron. Magician. Got him to 6 and decided... The pets seem weak (at 6, duh). The nukes are weaker than wizards, he sucks. I'll make a wizard. </P><P>#3 was Taroo. He went to 6 also and his extra 2-3 points per nuke didn't seem to be worth it as opposed to having a pet to root the monster and what not, he sucks too. </P><P>Back to Alagorn. Alagorn gets his L15 spells (cool! and levels quickly to 16 & 17. Then the itch hits. I want to make stuff blow up. I want it to go BOOM and have it turn and run from my magical might. (REALLY should have tried a necro at this point, DUH). And right about this time the raw silk recipies come out. And a friend wants to see a caster in raw silk. He's in Qeynos which is where Taroo is... </P><P>So I swap to Taroo and get him a fine new outfit of full raw silk, a pair of 15h/15m/2ac bracers & a fire crystal staff on young Taroo. These made a HUGE difference. at 6, 30 mana = 1 more nuke before dry. 30 hp means you can take 2-3 more rounds of damage since the damage is lessened by your full inventory slots of silk & bracers. Wheeeeeee.</P><P>6 to 20's a breeze. Then comes constant grouping and 20's fun too! Some of the funnest time in EQ was in Cazic over the next 15 or so levels. Grouping with (names removed). When I cast the 24 nuke on the lizards their HP halved. BOOM! Things going badly? nuke something to glowing embers. wheeeeeee! </P><P>Then around 28-29, life as a wizard changes. Yeah, you can now "kite like druids" with bonds of force, except, you don't get SOW to "double your chances". Your nukes are more and more resisted, the monsters you're killing are now: melee 2-3 rounds and you're dead. It sucked. I had a LOT of despair in this timeframe and wound up creating Feetsa around this time and twinking him all to hell.</P><P>All through Taroo's career, all he wanted to do was land the big nuke and watch the HP drain out of the HP bar. /rofl. Velious cured that notion. BOOM! 1120 damage... 1-2 pixels. So now, to "balance" us, we're getting "anti-gate" spells. I have those now. They're called Tishan's Clash, Markar's Clash, & Tishan's Discord. Heck, melee get anti-gate in bash & slam & a sword in the caster's face every second. /sigh. I just would like for people to go "wow. nice nuke" once in a while again. That hasn't happened in about 25 levels. </P><P>/shrug. Necro's are fun. Wizards can be, but to hear that the "braintrust" which is Verant has taken us from "Master of Damage" 2 years ago and made us "Master of Arcane Travel" just disgusts me. I made a wizard to blow stuff up, not to xloc people, not to stop monsters from gating (other than by blowing their asses up before they can gate), not to farm giants to buy twink gear for my alts. And yet... There I am, in OOT farming Gornit every once in a while. There I am port-whoring. There I am playing Ahkwell. How's that for the game's Vision. /sigh </P><P>As a wizard, I want to BLOW MOBS UP. I don't want a fancy Root. <BR>*****************************************</P><P>Wizards 51+ have the SAME problem Necro's do: Our core specialty is crap compared to what it was 1-50. Up to 50, we kill stuff. Post 50, I'm a taxi. </P><P>Taroo Fizonfyre (T.A.X.I.)<BR>(Travelus Arcanus Xpeditious Impressiveness)</P><P>Ahkwell Foley Really fun Necro</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
