        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I think it is great that wizards get this spell.  The wiz population, on MT anyway, is VERY small.  So is the necro pop so we're pretty much alike as it seems we both get the shaft, when it comes to uber levels.  Let's look at everyone else.  </P><P>Mages have their stupid super pets and their fire shields.  Druids have their share wolf form and sevreal group buff spells.  Shamans have group buffs, normal buffs, and are the buff kings.  Enchanters get clarity line, mezz, and haste spells.  Clerics are the grouping gods and you can never have too many.  Every melee is wanted, period.  Wizards can't do jack because if they nuke too much they are summoned and killed (no HS type spell).  If they do too little damage, they are labeled useless.  We are pretty much in the same boat.  </P><P>This new anti-gate thing is pretty much the same as our mana dump line.  Didn't ask for it, didn't know where it came from, has nothing to do with the class, and it will becomes our role in raids.  We should embrace our fellow sperned and not badgering them over some pathetic little spell they get.</P><P>BTW, if you could ever get a group of 6 wizards together with their dragon bane spells and 6 necs with trep (at least one out of 6 should stick plus instant recast)  and their pets....wizards do their damage absorbers and necros fear and do 6 augmentation pets....how's that for a waste land dragon butt kicking?  Of course you'd be lucky to get 6 level 60 wizards on at the same time more or less 6 60 wizards and 6 60 necros but it's a pleasent little thought.</P><P>~Taleldar Dreamslayer<BR>52nd DE Heretic<BR>Morell Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
