        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=40760&TOPIC_ID=5381&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=The+ultimate+blow+to+the+face%2E&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Here's my opinion on who is broken in the robe classes - it's more subjective than anything and heavily based on raid abilities:</P><P>Least Broken: Wizard - they can hit anything with their spells and are SUPER handy with trans and the new gate-stop spells.  Their problem which is the same for ALL robe classes - melee far outshines them.  However, the Bane spells are extremely helpful in our raids - our wizards each do 20-40K damage on some dragons.</P><P>My thoughts: I wouldn't play them with a friends account...soooooooo one-dimensional and boy do they die fast when they get aggro.  Thank you Harmshield!</P><P>Broken: Enchanters - It's tough to say enchanters are broken because they are a support/buff class and can land their critical slow and debuff spells on almost anything.  However, my sympathy for enchanters makes me say they're at least somewhat broken.</P><P>My thoughts: Please god...don't ever make me play an enchanter at a raid.  Trust me...if you think you're unhappy with your necro - play an enchater in a raid guild night in and night out.</P><P>Next Most Broken: Necromancer - Yup, we've got issues...our pets are in serious need of help, our core, class-defining ability (lifetaps) is next to useless on uber encounters.  That said, we shine in exp groups, small excursions and of course CR.</P><P>My thoughts: In my opinion, we are THE strongest overall robe class.  The most fun to play, with the greatest variety of abilities.  And, if they fix a few small things for us we will really shine.</P><P>Broke Broke Broke: Mage - It's tough to say mages are truly broken on the surface because they can land a number of spells and their pets are pretty tough (great epic weapon).  However, Call of Heroes and Mana Rods while being critical spells have completely transformed the mage class when it comes to raids.  Poor poor mages...factionless, COHing, Mana Rodding lumps on a log.</P><P>My thoughts: Thank god I don't play one.</P><P>Savan<BR>Afterlife</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
